This is an example of Full width graph.



::: {.callout-tip}
## Tip with Graphics
**column:** screen;
**out-width:** 100%;
**layout-ncol:** 4
:::


The following graph is gonna take 100% of the width, not only the text area width.






::: {.cell .column-screen layout-ncol="4"}

```{.r .cell-code}
library(patchwork)
library(ggplot2)

ggplot(mtcars) + geom_point(aes(mpg, disp))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-1-1.png){width=100%}
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(mtcars) + geom_boxplot(aes(gear, disp, group = gear))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-1-2.png){width=100%}
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(mtcars) + geom_smooth(aes(disp, qsec))
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula = 'y ~ x'
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-1-3.png){width=100%}
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(mtcars) + geom_bar(aes(carb))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
